                "invention-title": [
                    "Method for lowering charge level during blowing out of blast furnace",
                    "一种高炉停炉降料面的方法"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention relates to the technical field of blast furnace smelting, in particular to a blast furnace shut-down charge level lowering method which comprises the following steps: in the charge level lowering process, controlling the temperature of a furnace top below 350 DEG C by spraying liquid carbon dioxide on the furnace top, and keeping the volume percentage content of carbon dioxide in the furnace to be more than or equal to 35%, the volume percentage content of hydrogen to be less than or equal to 4% and the volume percentage content of oxygen to be less than or equal to 1%. The liquid carbon dioxide is sprayed from the furnace top instead of water spraying from the furnace top, so that hydrogen can be prevented from being generated; meanwhile, in the whole charge level descending process, the volume percentage content of carbon dioxide is kept to be 35% or above, water-gas reaction of water and coke does not exist in the ore reduction stage, and the oxygen content of the charge level is very low and can reach 1t; the percent is 0.5%, and the probability of coal gas detonation is greatly reduced; and secondly, even if the charge level is lowered to be below the bosh and enters a wind-oxygen excess stage, oxygen is very light in density and can quickly float upwards, and carbon dioxide can quickly sink, so that the surface of the charge is covered with the oxygen, and combustion of coal gas is prevented."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明涉及高炉冶炼技术领域，具体涉及一种高炉停炉降料面的方法，包括：在降料面过程中，通过炉顶喷洒液态二氧化碳将炉顶温度控制在350℃以下，同时保持炉内二氧化碳体积百分含量≥35％，氢气体积百分含量≤4％，氧气体积百分含量≤1％。本发明通过在炉顶喷出液态二氧化碳取代炉顶打水，能够杜绝氢气的产生；同时在整个料面下降过程中，将二氧化碳的体积百分含量保持在35％以上，在矿石还原阶段不存在水与焦炭的水煤气反应，料面氧含量很低，可以达到<0.5％，大大降低煤气爆震的概率；其次，即使降料面到炉腹以下，进入风氧过剩阶段，但氧气的密度很轻，会快速上浮，而二氧化碳会快速下沉，进而覆盖在炉料的表面，阻止煤气的燃烧。"
                }
            ]
